The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 22 December is 133,323 (15,366.3 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 17 December, there were 6,810 new confirmed cases (784.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 10 December, there were 5,337 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 28% (1,473 extra cases).
